dcterms:creator: R. J. LaLonde
dcterms:description: The LaLonde data is a dataset used to evaluate the effects of the National Supported Work Demonstration (NSW) program on earnings, comparing experimental and nonexperimental estimates.
dcterms:title: LaLonde Data

dcterms:creator: R. H. Dehejia
S. Wahba
dcterms:description: The LaLonde-Dehejia-Wahba (LDW) data is a subset of the original LaLonde data focusing on male participants, which includes additional pretreatment information to improve causal estimates.
dcterms:title: LaLonde-Dehejia-Wahba (LDW) Data

dcterms:creator: S. Calónico
J. Smith
dcterms:description: The Lalonde-Calónico-Smith (LCS) data reconstructs the female samples used in LaLonde's study, focusing on the effects of the NSW program on female participants.
dcterms:title: Lalonde-Calónico-Smith (LCS) Data

dcterms:creator: G. W. Imbens
D. B. Rubin
B. I. Sacerdote
dcterms:description: The IRS data examines the effects of lottery winnings on labor earnings, savings, and consumption, providing a clearer assignment mechanism for causal analysis.
dcterms:title: IRS Data

dcterms:description: The CPS-SSA data refers to the Current Population Survey - Social Security Administration data used in the context of LaLonde's analysis.
dcterms:title: CPS-SSA Data

dcterms:description: The PSID data refers to the Panel Study of Income Dynamics data used in the context of LaLonde's analysis.
dcterms:title: PSID Data
